sipProfile189Handling.desc:
Enable: when receiving 189/183 message 
combination from different legs, MGC need to 
send CPG with alerting and in-band          
info available information.               

Disable: when receiving 189/183 message 
combination from different legs, MGC ignore 
189.
sipProfile189Handling.name: sipProfile189Handling

sipProfileACgPNDisplayNameMapping.desc:
This is the flag for ACgPN PNP Mapping and 
Display Name PNP Mapping features.          
0     - The features are close and won??t 
be triggered.                               
1..31 - The features are open, and the value 
will be used as the number of the digits 
that triggers the two features.
sipProfileACgPNDisplayNameMapping.name: sipProfileACgPNDisplayNameMapping

sipProfileACgPNUserPartMapping.desc:
This is the flag for ACgPN PNP Mapping and 
User Part PNP Mapping features.
           
0: The features are disabled and will not be triggered. 
1..31: The features are enabled, and the 
value will be used as the number of the 
digits that triggers the two features.
sipProfileACgPNUserPartMapping.name: sipProfileACgPNUserPartMapping

sipProfileAllowMMTel.desc:
true: 
while MGC sends out message, MGC appends parameter <MMTel Value> of SIPProfile in Contact header and accept-Contact header.

While MGC receives INVITE and reINVITE, MGC will check whether parameter <MMTel Value> of SIPProfile and the MMTel value of accept-Contact header are identical, if they are different, MGC will reject the call. 

false(default): 
while MGC sends out message, MGC does not append parameter <MMTel Value> of SIPProfile in Contact header and accept-Contact header.

While MGC receives INVITE and reINVITE, MGC will check whether parameter <MMTel Value> of SIPProfile and the value of accept-Contact header are identical, if they are different, MGC will not reject the call, only ignore the feature.
sipProfileAllowMMTel.name: sipProfileAllowMMTel

sipProfileAllowNewCodecs.desc:
This attribute defines the new MGC behavior 
as below:

1) The complete codec list should be sent to 
the MGW for negotiation.                    
2) Also, the incoming codec list in the new 
SDP Offer must be sent down to the          
MGW in both the H.248 Local Descriptor and 
Remote Descriptor.                          

True - New Behavior
false - Old Behavior
sipProfileAllowNewCodecs.name: sipProfileAllowNewCodecs

sipProfileAnonymousURI.desc:
This specifies the way to express the Anonymous User Identity, used, for example, in the From header field to indicate that the caller identity is unknown.

0: Uses the 'unavailable@DomainName' format. The DomainName part is taken from the MGC SIP Domain Name. If MGC SIP Domain Name is set to 'operator1.net', the full SIP URI will be 'sip:unavailable@operator1.net'.

1: Uses the 'anonymous@anonymous.invalid' format. In this case, the full SIP URI is 'sip:anonymous@anonymous.invalid'.

2: Uses the 'unavailable@unknown.invalid' format. In this case, the full SIP URI is 'sip:unavailable@unknown.invalid'. 

3: Uses the 'unavailable@anonymous.invalid' format. In this case the full SIP URI is 'sip:unavailable@anonymous.invalid'.
sipProfileAnonymousURI.name: sipProfileAnonymousURI

sipProfileCallBusyCodeMapping.desc:
This parameter defines the SIP response code that is mapped from the ISUP cause code 17 (user busy). 
486: Map the ISUP cause code 17 (user busy) to the SIP response code 486.  
603: Map the ISUP cause code 17 (user busy) 
to the SIP response code 603. 
The default value is 486.
sipProfileCallBusyCodeMapping.name: sipProfileCallBusyCodeMapping

sipProfileCallResumeBehavior.desc:
Stateful (default):
Media direction in SDP offer for call resume 
is set according to current MGC local media 
state as in design base.

Stateless:
Media direction in SDP offer for call resume 
is always set to sendrecv.
sipProfileCallResumeBehavior.name: sipProfileCallResumeBehavior

sipProfileCodecAMROctetAlign.desc:
This parameters describes the default AMR 
mode used by the MGC for the outgoing SIP 
voice calls.                                

true: use octet-align mode
false: use Bandwidth Efficient mode
sipProfileCodecAMROctetAlign.name: sipProfileCodecAMROctetAlign

sipProfileCodecG729bDisable.desc:
To disable the G729 Annex B in the default 
SDP of MGC, set the value to 'true', 
otherwise set 'false' to it. This is one way 
to provide a control interface to operater 
to using codec G729 Annex B in the MGC.
sipProfileCodecG729bDisable.name: sipProfileCodecG729bDisable

sipProfileCodecs.desc:
This attribute defines the codecs supported by the profile in call.

Audio Codecs:

g711mLaw: G.711 mu-law scaling (PCMU RFC3551)

g711aLaw: G.711 A-law scaling (PCMA RFC3551)

g729a: G.729 Annex A (G729 RFC4749)

g7231: G.723.1 Dual-rate speech coder (G723 RFC3551)

gsmFr: GSM frame (GSM RFC3551)

gsmEfr: GSM enhanced frame (GSM-EFR RFC3551)

amr: Adaptive Multi-Rate (AMR RFC3267)

dtmfToneRelay: DTMF dual-tone multifrequency (telephone-event RFC4733)

g72624: G.726 24K (G726-24 RFC3551)

g72632: G.726 32K (G726-32 RFC3551)

g711aLawDynamic: G.711 A-law for V152

g711mLawDynamic: G.711 mu-law for V152

comfortNoise: Comfort noise (CN RFC3389)

clearMode: MIME type, a pseudo-codec (CLEARMODE RFC4040)

Video Codecs:

h263v1: MIMEtype H263 v1 (H263-1996 RFC2190)

h263v2: MIMEtype H263 v2 (H263-1998 RFC4629)

h263v3: MIMEtype H263 v3 (H263-2000 RFC4629)

mpeg4: MIMEtype MPEG-4 Visual(MP4V-ES RFC3016)

h264: H.264 (H264 RFC3984)

Data Codecs:

t38fax: MIME type, Internet Facsimile Protocol packets (t38 RFC3984)
sipProfileCodecs.name: sipProfileCodecs

sipProfileCodecsForInviteWithoutSDPOfMul.alias: Codecs For Invite Without SDP for Multimedia Call
sipProfileCodecsForInviteWithoutSDPOfMul.desc:
This attribute is a Codec Set.

When MGC receives an INVITE without SDP and the call is treated as a multimedia call(*), a default SDP is made up by this Codec Set.

*: This can be done by setting the How To Treat Invite Without SDP attribute to eTreatAsMultimediaCall.
sipProfileCodecsForInviteWithoutSDPOfMul.name: sipProfileCodecsForInviteWithoutSDPOfMultimediaCall

sipProfileDefaultIpSideAnumber.desc:
This value may hold a default calling number 
that overrides those 'A-numbers digits' 
received in the setup messages from IP side.
sipProfileDefaultIpSideAnumber.name: sipProfileDefaultIpSideAnumber

sipProfileDefaultIpSideAnumberNAI.desc: This attribute indicates the value of Nature of Address Indicator when the From Header Tel URL and Sip URI does not contain '+' at the beginning.
sipProfileDefaultIpSideAnumberNAI.name: sipProfileDefaultIpSideAnumberNAI

sipProfileDefaultIpSideAnumberPresInd.desc:
This attribute indicates the value of 
Address Presentation Restricted
Indicator when the default A number is used.
sipProfileDefaultIpSideAnumberPresInd.name: sipProfileDefaultIpSideAnumberPresInd

sipProfileDefaultIpSideAnumberUsage.desc:
The parameter defines the A-Number handling.

Use Default Always: The value of 'Default IP Side A-Number' is used as A-Number in the international format: +<country code><area code><subscriber number>.

Use Default If Not Received: The value of 'Default IP Side A-Number' is used as A-Number when A-Number in P-A-I is not received.

Use Nothing If Not Received: A-Number is empty when A-Number in P-A-I is not received.

Use From Header If Not Received: The user number of From Header is used as A-Number when A-Number in P-A-I is not received.
sipProfileDefaultIpSideAnumberUsage.name: sipProfileDefaultIpSideAnumberUsage

sipProfileDefaultRtpPacketTime.desc:
Default SDP a=ptime attribute, included in 
Add to MG for Local Descriptor at voice 
calls from PSTN to SIP.                     

This gives the length of time in 
milliseconds represented by the media in a  
packet.      

If value is equal to zero (0), the default 
value is not used.
sipProfileDefaultRtpPacketTime.name: sipProfileDefaultRtpPacketTime

sipProfileDiversionPrivacyHandling.desc:
This parameter defines how the privacy of 
the diversion header is handled.            

true: While Redirecting Indicator of 
Redirection Information is 'call rerouted, 
all?', 'privacy = full' is inserted to the 
diversion header.                           

false: While Redirecting Indicator of 
Redirection Information is 'call rerouted, 
all?', the privacy information is not 
inserted to the diversion header.
sipProfileDiversionPrivacyHandling.name: sipProfileDiversionPrivacyHandling

sipProfileDiversionType.desc:
This configuration parameter indicates which 
SIP Header is used to store the diversion 
information in both incoming and outgoing 
SIP messages when call diversion happens.   
The default  value is eDiversionHeader.
sipProfileDiversionType.name: sipProfileDiversionType

sipProfileDiversionUriScheme.desc: This attribute defines the URI scheme for diversion header sent to the sip server.
sipProfileDiversionUriScheme.name: sipProfileDiversionUriScheme

sipProfileENUMFailedUseRemoteServer.desc:
This variable will be used, when ENUM lookup 
has failed to determine whether remote SIP 
server shall be used to route calls. If set 
to true, then in case ENUM lookup has 
failed, the call will be routed to remote 
SIP server.
sipProfileENUMFailedUseRemoteServer.name: sipProfileENUMFailedUseRemoteServer

sipProfileENUMToContent.desc:
This attribute defines the value used in the 
To-field in outgoing INVITE after ENUM 
query. It can be either the same as 
request-uri (default) or the dialed B-number 
received by the MGC before ENUM.            
0 - same as request uri
1 - To field contains the dialed number 
before ENUM
sipProfileENUMToContent.name: sipProfileENUMToContent

sipProfileEarly183Enable.desc: This parameter defines if there is a 183 Session Progress be sent out just after initial INVITE with SDP received and before IAM is sent out.
sipProfileEarly183Enable.name: sipProfileEarly183Enable

sipProfileEarlyACMMapping.desc:
This attribute defines whether mapping ACM 
to SIP 18x while ACM with BCI Called party's 
status indicator =                          
No Indication and OBCI In-band information 
indicator = no indication.

true:
Map Early ACM to 183

false:
Not map the Early ACM
sipProfileEarlyACMMapping.name: sipProfileEarlyACMMapping

sipProfileEscapedHash.desc:
This parameters describes if the # character 
occurring in the Called Number will be 
escaped or not.                             

true:
For ISUP to SIP call, the # characters (if 
any) in the Called Number are escaped by 
MGC.                                        

For SIP to ISUP calls, MGC expects that the 
# characters (if any) in the Called Number 
are escaped by remote SIP node.             

false:
For ISUP to SIP call, the # characters (if 
any) in the Called Number are NOT escaped by 
MGC.                                        

For SIP to ISUP calls, MGC expects that the 
# characters (if any) in the Called Number 
are NOT escaped by remote SIP node.
sipProfileEscapedHash.name: sipProfileEscapedHash

sipProfileFaxMode.desc:
This parameter is only applicable when MRS based IM-MGW was selected and MGC try to initiate fax call setup.
VBD (eVBD):
  If VBD is selected, the MGC shall only handle the ANS notification from MRS based IM-MGW and initiate the G.711 fax call setup. MGC will return a successful response and take no further action if MGC received other notification.
T38 (eT38):
  If T38 is selected, the MGC shall only handle the v21flag notification from MRS based IM-MGW and initiate the T.38 fax call setup. MGC will return a successful response and take no further action if MGC received other notification.
T38 Preferred (eVBDandT38):
   If this option is selected, the MGC shall handle the early reached ANS notification from MRS based IM-MGW to trigger the G.711 fax call. If the V21 notification is later received MGC initiates the T.38 fax call setup.
sipProfileFaxMode.name: sipProfileFaxMode

sipProfileForwardSipNonRefreshment.name: sipProfileForwardSipNonRefreshment

sipProfileGetDisplayName.br:
If MGC is based on ANSI ISUP, this attribute 
will be available; else this attribute 
should only be Not Get DisplayName.
sipProfileGetDisplayName.desc:
This attribute indicates MGC how to get 
'display-name' from 
'P-Asserted-Identity' or 'from' header. 
In ANSI ISUP outgoing call, the 
'display-name' info will set to Calling 
Name (Generic Name parameter). This 
attribute is only available for ANSI ISUP.

o Not Get DisplayName (0)- Not get 
'display-name' from  SIP header. 

o Get from P-A-I or From header (1) - Get 
'display-name' from 'P-A-I', or 'from' 
header if 'display-name' is not received in 
'P-A-I' header.                          

o Get from P-A-I header (2) - Get 
'display-name' from 'P-A-I'.                

o Get from From header(3) - Get 
'display-name' from 'from' header.          

Note:
  P-A-I means P-Asserted-Identity.
sipProfileGetDisplayName.name: sipProfileGetDisplayName

sipProfileH245InitializationTimer.desc:
The parameter defines the supervision time 
for capability exchange procedures and 
master slave determination procedures 
towards H324 terminal, and capability 
exchange procedures from H324 terminal.
     
The timer is started when the procedures are 
initiated towards H324 terminal.
            
The timer is stopped when the procedures are 
completed.
                                  
If the timer expires, the messages are sent 
again. After three retransmission, if the 
timer expires, the call is released.
sipProfileH245InitializationTimer.name: sipProfileH245InitializationTimer

sipProfileH245OpenLogicalChannelsTimer.desc:
The parameter defines the supervision time 
for open logical channels procedures and 
multiplex table procedures towards H324 
terminal.
                                   
The timer is started when the procedures are 
initiated towards H324 terminal.
            
The timer is stopped when the procedures are 
completed.
                                  
If the timer expires the call is released.
sipProfileH245OpenLogicalChannelsTimer.name: sipProfileH245OpenLogicalChannelsTimer

sipProfileHoldResume.desc:
If Hold service initiated by the PSTN side 
after call established, MGC can map the     
ISUP CPG Hold or Retrieve message to the 
UPDATE or re-INVITE request.   
              
o ReinviteAlways  Always send re-INVITE.

o UpdatePrior     Send UPDATE if remote SIP 
side support the UPDATE,otherwise send 
re-INVITE instead.       
                   
o UpdateAlways    Send UPDATE if remote SIP 
side support the UPDATE,otherwise ignore the 
Hold request and not generate the 
corresponding SIP request.

o NoMapping    Terminate Call Hold/Resume CPG message coming from PSTN side, and do not map it to SIP message towards IMS side.
sipProfileHoldResume.name: sipProfileHoldResume

sipProfileHowToProcessVideoCallFromSIP.alias: How To Process Video Call From SIP
sipProfileHowToProcessVideoCallFromSIP.desc:
This parameter is used to control how to handle an incoming INVITE with audio and video codecs in SIP to SIP-I interworking scenario.

IpIp Normal Call(eIpIpNormalCall):
  MGC acts as a B2BUA for conversion between SIP and SIP-I. SDP is passed transparently from one side to the other side. Media is transmitted between two sides directly and no MGW involved.

3G324M call over clearmode codec over RTP(eClearmodeDataCall):
  MGC acts as a B2BUA for conversion between SIP and SIP-I (CS side). In SIP-I only the clearmode codec is included in SDP. H.245, audio and video are multiplexed by H.223 and transmitted over RTP by using clearmode codec.
sipProfileHowToProcessVideoCallFromSIP.name: sipProfileHowToProcessVideoCallFromSIP

sipProfileHowToTreatClearmodeCall.desc:
This attribute has two options,

eTreatAsVoiceTransitCall(0):
When select this value, it means when 
receives a call from IP side with clearmode 
codec, the media type is treated as a Data 
Call, but in fact it is a Voice Transit Call 
using clearmode codec.                      



eTreatAsMultimediaTransitCall(1):
When select this value, it means when 
receives a call from IP side with clearmode 
codec, the media type is treated as a Data 
Call, but in fact it is a Multimedia Transit 
Call using clearmode codec.                  

Default value:eTreatAsVoiceTransitCall(0)
sipProfileHowToTreatClearmodeCall.name: sipProfileHowToTreatClearmodeCall

sipProfileHowToTreatInviteWithoutSDP.alias: How To Treat Invite Without SDP
sipProfileHowToTreatInviteWithoutSDP.desc:
This attribute is to indicate how to treat 
call type when receive a INVITE without the 
SDP:                                        

eTreatAsVoiceCall(0): Handle incoming 
initial INVITE without SDP as VoIP call     

eTreatAsMultimediaCall(1): Handle incoming 
initial INVITE without SDP as multimedia 
call.                                       

Default value is eTreatAsVoiceCall(0).
sipProfileHowToTreatInviteWithoutSDP.name: sipProfileHowToTreatInviteWithoutSDP

sipProfileHowToTreatNoPEarlyMedia.desc:
This is information for MGC on handling 
through connect procedures if no 
P-Early-Media Header is present in the 
received INVITE.                             

o Through-Connect(0) : Always through 
Connect                                     

o NoThrough-connect(1) : No through 
Connection
sipProfileHowToTreatNoPEarlyMedia.name: sipProfileHowToTreatNoPEarlyMedia

sipProfileHowToUseRemoteDynamicPT.alias: How To Use Remote Dynamic Payload Type
sipProfileHowToUseRemoteDynamicPT.desc:
It defines how to handle received remote dynamic payload type in SDP answer.

Use Remote Dynamic PT(eUseRemoteDynamicPT) -- use remote PT for sending and receiving RTP.

No Use Remote Dynamic PT(eNoUseRmoteDynamicPT) -- use local PT (in SDP offer)for receiving and remote PT for sending (comply with RFC3264).
sipProfileHowToUseRemoteDynamicPT.name: sipProfileHowToUseRemoteDynamicPT

sipProfileIpSideAnumberRestriction.desc:
This attribute determines if the MGC should 
pass the 'A-number' received in the setup 
message from IP side to PSTN in case the     
'Default IP Side A-Number' is not defined.

o   NumberAllowed (1):  
'A-numbers' are passed.  If presentation 
restricted indication is received from IP 
side, the 'Presentation restricted' is set 
in the Calling Number to PSTN. 
              
o  NumberRestricted (2):
If presentation restricted indication is not 
received from IP side, the 'A-number' is   
passed.   If presentation restricted 
indication is received from IP side, the 
'A-number' is not passed and  'address not 
available' is indicated to PSTN.             

o NumberInhibited:
'A-number' is not passed. The 'address not 
available' is indicated to PSTN.
sipProfileIpSideAnumberRestriction.name: sipProfileIpSideAnumberRestriction

sipProfileIpSideConnectedNumberRestricti.desc:
This attribute is the indicator to decide 
the method of mapping from SIP P-A-I and 
privacy header to CoN parameter.
sipProfileIpSideConnectedNumberRestricti.name: sipProfileIpSideConnectedNumberRestriction

sipProfileIpSideRedirectionInfoRestricti.desc:
This attribute determines if the MGC should 
pass the 'Redirection Info' received from IP 
side to PSTN.
sipProfileIpSideRedirectionInfoRestricti.name: sipProfileIpSideRedirectionInfoRestriction

sipProfileLCPriorityForNonPriorityCalls.desc:
Required for Load control for value of 
priority for non priority call.
sipProfileLCPriorityForNonPriorityCalls.name: sipProfileLCPriorityForNonPriorityCalls

sipProfileLCPriorityForPriorityAndEmerge.alias: LC Priority For Priority And Emergency Calls
sipProfileLCPriorityForPriorityAndEmerge.desc:
Required for Load control for priority value 
of priority and emergency call
sipProfileLCPriorityForPriorityAndEmerge.name: sipProfileLCPriorityForPriorityAndEmergencyCalls

sipProfileLockOneCodec.desc:
The parameter only is used for IM-MGw.

case1::when MGC answers sdp, MGC only send one codec.
case2::after SDP answer,if MGC receives more than one codec, MGC will send a reinvite with only one codec for locking codec
sipProfileLockOneCodec.name: sipProfileLockOneCodec

sipProfileMMCallSequenceType.desc:
This parameter defines if the video call setup sequence should be slow start, fast start or middle start.

Fast Start(eFastStart):
  H.245 negotiation is done before connection.
Slow Start (eSlowStart):
  H.245 negotiation is done after connection, and MGC sends initial INVITE without SDP. 
Middle Start (eMiddleStart):
  H.245 negotiation is done after connection, and MGC sends initial INVITE with SDP (MGC reserves audio and video resource from MGW according to MGC local codec configuration.).
sipProfileMMCallSequenceType.name: sipProfileMMCallSequenceType

sipProfileMMTelTag.desc:
value:
  MGC will treat the value as mmtel feature tag in Accept-Contact header, if the value is different from the value of Accept-Contact header, MGC will reject the call while customer set parameter <Allow MMTel> of SIPProfile as true.
sipProfileMMTelTag.name: sipProfileMMTelTag

sipProfileMinimumAmountOfBnumber.desc:
Minimum Amount Of B-number for overlapping in SIPI to SIP call.

If the B-number is less than the minimum amount of digits to route a call, MGC starts T35 and waits until the minimum amount of digits that can represent a telephone number is received (or a stop digit is received).  If T35 expires before the minimum amount of digits (or a stop digit) has been received, a REL is sent to the SS side.
However, there are cases when the gateway cannot know whether the number received is a complete number or not.  In this case, the gateway should collect digits until a timer (T10) expires or a stop digit is entered by the user.
sipProfileMinimumAmountOfBnumber.name: sipProfileMinimumAmountOfBnumber

sipProfileMsgIdForNoCommonCodec.alias: Msg ID For No Common Codec
sipProfileMsgIdForNoCommonCodec.desc:
This parameter is not applicable if the MGC workMode parameter is set to 'Always use media gateway' (0).
If the workMode is set to 'Smart mode' (1), a received SIP response code will be compared with the value given to this parameter. If they are equal, MGC will re-establish the call by using the MGW. If they are not equal, the call will be released.
sipProfileMsgIdForNoCommonCodec.name: sipProfileMsgIdForNoCommonCodec

sipProfileName.desc:
The user defined identification of the
profile.
sipProfileName.name: sipProfileName

sipProfileNumberOfRedirectionsAllowed.desc:
This field will hold the number of
allowed redirections done by the MGC
for an outgoing call. If this parameter
is set to 0, the call forwarding is
prohibited and attempts from an IP side
redirection server will result as failed
calls.

Config information, number of allowed
SIP redirections for calls using this
profile.
sipProfileNumberOfRedirectionsAllowed.name: sipProfileNumberOfRedirectionsAllowed

sipProfileOaidTaidDeprecation.desc: Deprecate the OAID/TAID parameter in SIP P-Charing-Vector header, accordingly OAID and TAID would not be presented in Radius/Diameter charging request.
sipProfileOaidTaidDeprecation.name: sipProfileOaidTaidDeprecation

sipProfileOriginAnumber.desc:
The A-Number origin parameter. It is used as 
input for A-Number analysis, in pre-analysis 
phase.                                 
The attribute is used when MGC is receiving 
a call from IP side.
sipProfileOriginAnumber.name: sipProfileOriginAnumber

sipProfileOriginBnumber.desc:
This attribute is the input the B-number 
pre-analysis. It gives the possibility to 
get different analysis results for the same 
B-number.                                   

This attribute is used when MGC is receiving 
a call from IP side
sipProfileOriginBnumber.name: sipProfileOriginBnumber

sipProfileOutgoingNetwork.desc:
This parameter defines to which network the 
the MGC shall send the SIP messages from 
outgoing SIP calls that have been initiated 
through this profile. If the profile is used 
for serving the received SIP calls, the SIP 
messages are always sent to the network 
from which the INVITE has been received.

The default value is 1. Network 1 is the 
only network needed in normal PSTN 
GW installations. It is also considered 
as the 'own network' in IP-to-IP traffic 
cases where the MGC is configured to 
route SIP traffic between the 'own 
network' and the 'other network'.  In those 
cases, network number 2 is used for 
indicating the 'other network'.
sipProfileOutgoingNetwork.name: sipProfileOutgoingNetwork

sipProfileOutgoingPrecondition.desc: This parameter defines whether precondition information is contained in outgoing INVITE message.
sipProfileOutgoingPrecondition.name: sipProfileOutgoingPrecondition

sipProfilePEarlyMedia.desc:
This attribute indicates whether MGC 
supports P-Early Media or not.
sipProfilePEarlyMedia.name: sipProfilePEarlyMedia

sipProfilePSTNXMLSupport.desc: The parameter indicates whether the PSTN XML feature is enabled for the sessions arriving at the profile from the SIP side.
sipProfilePSTNXMLSupport.name: sipProfilePSTNXMLSupport

sipProfilePreconditionCurDirChk.desc:
The parameter is used to control how to check precondition current direction if an initial INVITE with precondition is received.

If set to true MGC will check if the precondition current direction is compatible with the direction attribute in SDP, otherwise no checking is made.

By default, the parameter is set to false.
sipProfilePreconditionCurDirChk.name: sipProfilePreconditionCurDirChk

sipProfilePreferredTransportProtocol.desc:
This parameter defines the preferred 
transport protocol to be used for sessions 
initiated by the MGC unless the transport 
protocol to be used is provided using other 
mechanisms (i.e. ENUM DNS lookup).
sipProfilePreferredTransportProtocol.name: sipProfilePreferredTransportProtocol

sipProfilePrioritizeCodecs.desc:
This attribute defines if the codecs in SDP 
Offer must be prioritized according to the 
MoSipCodecPriority before sending SDP to MG.
This is used only in audio calls (and in 
initial codec reservation for video calls).
sipProfilePrioritizeCodecs.name: sipProfilePrioritizeCodecs

sipProfilePrivacyOIPTIP.desc:
The parameter defines if SIP Privacy header with value 'none' will be included in outgoing INVITE for OIP case or in 200OK for TIP case.

Privacy header with 'none' (ePrivacyNoneForOIPTIP) --- Privacy involves value 'none' when CgPN APRI or CoN APRI is 'presentation allowed'
No Privacy header(ePrivacyOmitForOIPTIP) --- Privacy omitted when CgPN APRI or CoN APRI is 'presentation allowed'
sipProfilePrivacyOIPTIP.name: sipProfilePrivacyOIPTIP

sipProfilePstnSideAnumberAreaCode.desc:
This attribute defines the area code,
which will be included in A number in
PSTN-SIP call if the A number received
from PSTN has local significance
(subscriber number).

Valid digits are 0..9
sipProfilePstnSideAnumberAreaCode.name: sipProfilePstnSideAnumberAreaCode

sipProfilePstnSideAnumberCountryCode.desc:
This attribute defines the country code, 
which will be included in A number in 
PSTN-SIP call if the A number received
from PSTN has national significance.

Valid digits are 0..9
sipProfilePstnSideAnumberCountryCode.name: sipProfilePstnSideAnumberCountryCode

sipProfilePstnSideAnumberPassed.desc:
This attribute defines whether the 
Additional Calling Party Number (ACgPN) / 
Calling Party Number (CgPN) will be passed 
in the From header / P-AssertedIdentity (in 
a PSTN-SIP call) if the Nature of Address 
Indicator is other than the following:      

- International Number
- National (Significant) Number
- Subscriber Number
sipProfilePstnSideAnumberPassed.name: sipProfilePstnSideAnumberPassed

sipProfilePstnSideAnumberRestriction.desc:
This attribute determines how the A number 
restriction is handled for outgoing calls 
using this profile.

o NumberAllowed (1):
the calling number is always passed if 
available. If 'Presentation restricted' is 
set in Calling Party Number from PSTN, the 
anonymous caller's identification is 
indicated in IP side.

o NumberRestricted (2):
If 'Presentation restricted' is not set in 
Calling Party Number from PSTN, the
Calling Number is passed on.
If 'Presentation restricted' is set in 
Calling Party Number from PSTN, the 
Calling Number is not passed and the 
display name indicates 'Unknown'.

o NumberInhibited (3):
the Calling Number is never passed and 
the caller is indicated to be unknown.

sipProfileRnFormat.desc:
This indicates the format of the received RN or the sent RN in the initial INVITE.

Short Form Routing Number: Only includes the routing number.

Full Form Routing Number: Includes the routing number followed by the user part.

Mixed Form Routing Number: Includes the routing number mixed with the user part.

When MGC receives the initial INVITE, if the parameter is Short Form Routing Number, MGC considers the received RN only includes the routing number. For example, ';rn=+1-1234' is the received RN. The routing number is '1234'. '+1' is the country code.

If the parameter is Full Form Routing Number, MGC considers the received RN is the routing number followed by the Tel URI user part. For example, ';rn=+1-1234-1111' is the received RN. The routing number is '1234', and the user part is '1111'.

If the parameter is Mixed Form Routing Number, MGC considers the received RN is the routing number mixed with the Tel URI user part. For example, ';rn=+49-21-123D-1111' is the received RN. The routing number is '123D', and the user part is '21-1111'. '+49' is the country code.

When MGC sends the initial INVITE, if the parameter is Short Form Routing Number, the sent RN should be the routing number. For example, the sent RN is ';rn=+1-1234'.

If the parameter is Full Form Routing Number or Mixed Form Routing Number, the sent RN should be the routing number followed by the Tel URI user part. For example, the sent RN is ';rn=+1-1234-1111'.
sipProfileRnFormat.name: sipProfileRnFormat

sipProfileSdpAnswerHandling.desc:

SDP Always - means that SDP shall be sent out duplicate in 18x or final 200 response once it has been sent out before.
SDP Not Always - means that SDP shall not be sent out in 18x or final 200 response once it has been sent out reliably before.

1: Uses the 'anonymous@anonymous.invalid' format. In this case, the full SIP URI is 'sip:anonymous@anonymous.invalid'.

2: Uses the 'unavailable@unknown.invalid' format. In this case, the full SIP URI is 'sip:unavailable@unknown.invalid'.

sipProfileUseIsupTransparency.desc:
For outgoing SIP sessions this parameter 
defines if ISUP transparency is allowed for 
the specific SIP profile. If the ISUP 
Route's routeTrafficType indicates that ISUP 
transparency shall be used but the SIP 
profile does not allow it (No) the session 
setup will be terminated.                   
If the ISUP Route's routeTrafficType 
indicates that ISUP transparency is not used 
but the SIP profile requires it (Required) 
the session setup will also be terminated. 
If the value is 'Allowed' ISUP transparency 
will be used if the ISUP Route's 
routeTrafficType indicates so, but the 
session setup will continue also without 
ISUP transparency.                          

For incoming SIP sessions this parameter 
defines if the use of ISUP transparency is 
required by the remote SIP node. If the 
initial INVITE SIP message contains an ISUP 
MIME message body and the value is 'No' the 
session setup will be terminated if the 
Content-Disposition handling parameter is 
'required'. If the value is 'optional' the 
session setup will continue, but without 
ISUP transparency. If the value is 
'Required' the session setup will be 
terminated unless the SIP message contains 
an ISUP MIME message body. If the value is 
'Allowed' the session setup will continue 
both if there is an ISUP MIME message body 
in the initial INVITE SIP message or not.

'eForceSIP'
In incoming side, indicate MGC only support 
SIP call using this profile. SIP-I 
transparency call will be released. Be same 
to 'No'.                                    
                   
In outgoing side, indicate MGC will force to raise SIP call.                       

'eForceSIP-I'
In incoming side, indicate MGC only support 
SIP-I transparency call using this profile. 
SIP call will be released. Be same to       
'Required'.

In outgoing side, indicate MGC will force to raise SIP-I call.
sipProfileUseIsupTransparency.name: sipProfileUseIsupTransparency

sipProfileWaitTwoStageAddressTimer.desc:

Stage Address e.g. e-mail address, when 
using H.245 based two stage dialling for
3G324M to SIP multimedia calls.             
             
The timer is started at sending CON message
to ISUP network. It is stopped at
reception of valid Two Stage Address         
in H.245 message UserIputIndication.         

If the timer expires, the call is released.

If the timer is set to value zero (0), H245 
based two stage dialling is not in use. 
The call is immediately released, if a 
two stage dialling call is made and ISUP 
message IAM does not contain valid two stage 
address.

The default value is 5000 milliseconds.
sipProfileWaitTwoStageAddressTimer.name: sipProfileWaitTwoStageAddressTimer

sipRespCodeMapId.alias: SIP Response Code Mapping Table Index
sipRespCodeMapId.desc:
Range: Min = 0; Max = 32;
Valid characters: A-Z,a-z,0-9,.,-,/,_ 

This table defines mapping rules from SIP final failure response code (4xx~6xx) to ISUP Q.850 cause code in REL message.

This table will not take effect while existing the following cases:
(1). SIP message contains ISUP MIME body with REL message which contains Q.850 cause code;
(2). SIP message contains Reason header with Q.850 cause code.

If the cause code mapping is defined in this table, such mapping rule will be followed by MGC, otherwise the mapping defined in 3GPP TS 29.163 v8.8.0 will be followed. The mapping rule defined in this table will not affect the mapping for ACR, CCBS and CCNR.

If the cause code has been defined in this table,but the same cause code has also been defined in ACR Code,then this table will not take effect and ACR code will be applied.
sipRespCodeMapId.name: sipRespCodeMapId

'display-name' of                           
'from' header according to the ANSI ISUP's 
Calling Name info.                          

o Set to P-A-I and From header (3) - Set 
'display-name' of                           
both 'P-A-I'  and 'from' header according to 
the ANSI ISUP's Calling Name info.          

Note:
  P-A-I means P-Asserted-Identity.

mgcPmSipIRejIncoCallAttempts.description:
The number of incoming SIP call attempts 
discarded due to:                           
- received INVITE contained no ISUP MIME, 
but used SIP profile requires SIP-I
        
- received INVITE/ISUP MIME had the handling 
set to required, but used SIP profile does 
not support SIP-I                           

- received INVITE contained a version/base 
of ISUP that is not supported by the MGC
mgcPmSipIRejIncoCallAttempts.name: mgcPmSipIRejIncoCallAttempts
mgcPmSipIRejIncoCallAttempts.title: Number of incoming SIP call attempts discarded due to SIP-I mismatch

mgcPmSipIRejOutgCallAttempts.description:
The number of outgoing SIP call attempts 
discarded due to that the ISUP does not 
support transit traffic (traffic type B) and 
SIP-I is set as required in used SIP 
profile.
mgcPmSipIRejOutgCallAttempts.name: mgcPmSipIRejOutgCallAttempts
mgcPmSipIRejOutgCallAttempts.title: Number of outgoing SIP call attempts discarded due to SIP-I mismatch

mgcPmSipTotAddressIncomplete.description:
Total number of session establishment 
request failures due to address incomplete.
This counter is used only for incoming
sessions. It is incremented when a 484
response is sent.
mgcPmSipTotAddressIncomplete.name: mgcPmSipTotAddressIncomplete
mgcPmSipTotAddressIncomplete.title: Total number of rejected session setups due to incomplete address

mgcPmSipTotClientError.description:
Total number of session establishment 
request failures with client error as a 
status codes. This counter is used only for
incoming sessions. It is incremented when
a 4xx response is sent.
mgcPmSipTotClientError.name: mgcPmSipTotClientError
mgcPmSipTotClientError.title: Total number of rejected session setups due to client error status

mgcPmSipTotCurrentSessions.description:
Number of current sessions, both incoming 
and outgoing sessions. This gauge           
is incremented when a session has been
successfully established and decremented 
when                                        
the session has been terminated.
mgcPmSipTotCurrentSessions.name: mgcPmSipTotCurrentSessions
mgcPmSipTotCurrentSessions.title: Number of current sessions, successful setup and release

mgcPmSipTotEndUserBusy.description:
The total number of session establishment 
request failures due to end-user busy.
This counter is used only for incoming
sessions. It is incremented when a 486 or
600 response is sent.
mgcPmSipTotEndUserBusy.name: mgcPmSipTotEndUserBusy
mgcPmSipTotEndUserBusy.title: Total number of release due to end user busy

mgcPmSipTotFailedDue2SdTimeout.description:
Total number of failed session attempts due 
to 2 stage dialing timeout.
mgcPmSipTotFailedDue2SdTimeout.name: mgcPmSipTotFailedDue2SdTimeout
mgcPmSipTotFailedDue2SdTimeout.title: Total number of failed session attempts due to 2SD timeout

mgcPmSipTotFailedDueH245Timeout.description:
Total number of failed session attempts due 
to H.245 timeout towards the 3G.324M.
mgcPmSipTotFailedDueH245Timeout.name: mgcPmSipTotFailedDueH245Timeout
mgcPmSipTotFailedDueH245Timeout.title: Total number of failed session attempts due to H.245 timeout

mgcPmSipTotFailureDueOtherReason.description:
Total number of session establishment 
request failures due other reasons those 
that are indicated with the other counters. 
This counter is used only for incoming 
sessions. It is indicated when 'any other'
response code is sent. That is, a response
code that does not cause increment of 
any other PM counter defined for the
specific  SIP error codes sent from the
MGC node.
mgcPmSipTotFailureDueOtherReason.name: mgcPmSipTotFailureDueOtherReason
mgcPmSipTotFailureDueOtherReason.title: Total number of released sessions due to other reasons

mgcPmSipTotIncomingSessionIncompatibleCo.description:
Total number of incoming SIP sessions 
rejected because of not matching codecs.
mgcPmSipTotIncomingSessionIncompatibleCo.name: mgcPmSipTotIncomingSessionIncompatibleCodecs
mgcPmSipTotIncomingSessionIncompatibleCo.title: Total number of inco. SIP sessions rejected due to unmatching  codecs

mgcPmSipTotIncomingSessions.description:
Total number of incoming SIP sessions, 
including failed session setup attempts 
received by the MGCF. This counter is 
incremented whenever SIP INVITE message is 
received for a new session, i.e. the 
possible re-INVITEs received during an 
ongoing session do not increment this 
counter.
mgcPmSipTotIncomingSessions.name: mgcPmSipTotIncomingSessions
mgcPmSipTotIncomingSessions.title: Total number of successful and rejected SIP sessions

mgcPmSipTotIncomingSuccesfullSessions.description:
Total number of incoming successful SIP 
sessions. A successful session establishment 
is an INVITE received for a new session
for which a 200 OK is sent and ACK is 
received.
mgcPmSipTotIncomingSuccesfullSessions.name: mgcPmSipTotIncomingSuccesfullSessions
mgcPmSipTotIncomingSuccesfullSessions.title: Total number of incoming successful SIP sessions

mgcPmSipTotInternalError.description:
Total number of session establishment 
request failures due to internal server 
error. This counter is used only for
incoming sessions. It is incremented when
a 500, 502 or 504 response is sent.
mgcPmSipTotInternalError.name: mgcPmSipTotInternalError
mgcPmSipTotInternalError.title: Total number of rejected SIP sessions due to internal server error

mgcPmSipTotInvalidAddress.description:
Total number of session establishment 
request failures due to invalid address.
This counter is used only for incoming
sessions. It is incremented when a
404, 410, 414, 416, 485 or 604 response
is sent.
mgcPmSipTotInvalidAddress.name: mgcPmSipTotInvalidAddress
mgcPmSipTotInvalidAddress.title: Total number of rejected incoming setups due to invalid address

mgcPmSipTotInviteRequestReceived.description:
Total number of received INVITE requests.
                                   
The counter is incremented for all received
INVITE requests, also for re-INVITE requests
received during an ongoing session.
mgcPmSipTotInviteRequestReceived.name: mgcPmSipTotInviteRequestReceived
mgcPmSipTotInviteRequestReceived.title: Total number of received INVITE requests

mgcPmSipTotOutgoingSessionIncompatibleCo.description:
Total number of outgoing SIP sessions 
rejected because of not matching codecs.
mgcPmSipTotOutgoingSessionIncompatibleCo.name: mgcPmSipTotOutgoingSessionIncompatibleCodecs
mgcPmSipTotOutgoingSessionIncompatibleCo.title: Total number of rejected SIP sessions due to no matching codec

mgcPmSipTotOutgoingSessions.description:
Total number of outgoing SIP sessions, 
including failed session setups with a SIP 
INVITE message sent from the MGCF.
mgcPmSipTotOutgoingSessions.name: mgcPmSipTotOutgoingSessions
mgcPmSipTotOutgoingSessions.title: Total number of successfully or rejected outgoing SIP sessions

mgcPmSipTotOutgoingSessionsRedirected.description:
Total number of outgoing sessions redirected 
to other destination with SIP 3xx responses.
mgcPmSipTotOutgoingSessionsRedirected.name: mgcPmSipTotOutgoingSessionsRedirected
mgcPmSipTotOutgoingSessionsRedirected.title: Total number of SIP 3xx redirecting responses

mgcPmSipTotOutgoingSuccesfullSessions.description:

mgcPmSipTotOutgoingSuccesfullSessions.name: mgcPmSipTotOutgoingSuccesfullSessions
mgcPmSipTotOutgoingSuccesfullSessions.title: Total number of outgoing successful SIP sessions

mgcPmSipTotServerCapacityMismatch.description:
Total number of session establishment 
request failures due to server capacity 
mismatches. This counter is used only for 
incoming sessions only. It is incremented
when a 405, 413, 415, 488, 501, 505, 513
or 606 response is sent.
mgcPmSipTotServerCapacityMismatch.name: mgcPmSipTotServerCapacityMismatch
mgcPmSipTotServerCapacityMismatch.title: Total number of rejected setups due to server capacity mismatches

mgcPmSipTotServerCongestion.description:
Total number of session establishment 
request failures due to server congestion.
The counter is used only for incoming
sessions. It is incremented when a 503
response is sent.
mgcPmSipTotServerCongestion.name: mgcPmSipTotServerCongestion
mgcPmSipTotServerCongestion.title: Total number of rejected session setups due to server congestion

mgcPmSipTotUnsuccesfulINVITEs.description:
Total number of unsuccessful INVITE 
attempts received. This counter is used only
for  incoming sessions. It is incremented 
when a 3xx, 4xx, 5xx, or 6xx response is 
sent.
mgcPmSipTotUnsuccesfulINVITEs.name: mgcPmSipTotUnsuccesfulINVITEs
mgcPmSipTotUnsuccesfulINVITEs.title: Total number of unsuccessful INVITE attempts received

mgcPmSipTotUnsupportedScheme.description:
Total number of Request URIs received with 
unsupported scheme. This counter is used 
only for incoming sessions.
mgcPmSipTotUnsupportedScheme.name: mgcPmSipTotUnsupportedScheme
mgcPmSipTotUnsupportedScheme.title: Total number of Request URIs received with unsupported scheme

mgcPmSipTotUserNotAvailable.description:
Total number of session establishment
request failures due to user not available.
This counter is used only for incoming
sessions. It is incremented when a 480
response is sent.
mgcPmSipTotUserNotAvailable.name: mgcPmSipTotUserNotAvailable
mgcPmSipTotUserNotAvailable.title: Total number of rejected session setups due to user not available
